summary: I never knew what I wanted to do. I studied law, human resources, I had a job at a bank, it was shitty. And one day in the...
caption:
I never knew what I wanted to do. I studied law, human resources, I had a job at a bank, it was shitty. And one day in the street, I was scouted as a model. That allowed me to make some money, and one morning, two and a half years ago, I woke up and I told myself: “Oh yeah, I’d like to be an actor.” I enrolled at a school, and I started the next day. And that’s all I’ve been doing since.

Happy 26th Birthday, Maxence Danet Fauvel! (June 27, 1993)

To Maxence, 
We may never meet in this lifetime but I want to say, thank you for being born. You were meant to do great...
body:
💌:

To Maxence,

We may never meet in this lifetime but I want to say, thank you for being born. You were meant to do great things and inspire those in need. And that was what you did for me and many others. To have you as a character that is so well loved and so relatable to so many individuals can be overwhelming but I see how much you love portraying Eliott Demaury. The love and passion you put in your work has paid off and will pay off. Again, I want to thank you for your kindness and your consideration of this special character that holds a dear place in our hearts. I wish you a happy birthday and I hope this year, you will grow into a better version of yourself and that you keep thriving off of positivity and success that will come your way. We love you and take care of yourself now.

—With love from one of your many admirers, G.

P.S. You are sunshine when you smile, happy birthday.

summary: Pick your favorite clipe between: samedi 09:17 or vendredi 18:35
question: Pick your favorite clipe between: samedi 09:17 or vendredi 18:35
answer: I’m going to have to say samedi 9h17, because it’s a longer clip that shows and tells us so much more about them as characters. You see them actually talk about their coping mechanisms, talk about their experience in love/with guys, talk about what they thought when they first saw each other. And between the talking there are all those soft scenes where they kiss and just are together in the soft daylight. Don’t get me wrong, I really love vendredi 18h35, but if you are making me choose I go for samedi 9h17.
